{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_206","type":"agent_message","text":"The trace-enabled build exposed a bigger issue than metadata: the native-image classpath is mixing Gradle’s bundled Groovy `4.0.28` jars from `localGroovy()` with the tested library `4.0.24`. That explains the `groovy-datetime` module warnings and makes the remaining indy crash much more suspect as a test classpath problem rather than a library metadata gap. I’m checking whether the test can compile and run purely against the library’s own Groovy dependency so I can remove the version skew."}}
